issue_comments.body:
@sevilbk-trimble I believe I have addressed this issue (or at least accounted for it) in #10481.

Please test if this still needs to be addressed. We need to be very confident that this does not break the Site Capture processing and that all stations + annotations are properly positioned for multiple PDF rotations.

If you Westminster Campus drawing has a 90degree rotation and NREL-EMAPS-level1(Full-res).pdf has a 0degree rotation.

files.patch:
@@ -960,37 +960,35 @@ private Point TransformToPdfPoint(double directionX, double directionY, NativePa
             var width = cropBox.Width();
             var height = cropBox.Height();

-            // Scale and transform per rotation.
+            // De-normalize coordinates against the physical (unrotated) page dimensions.
             // directionX/Y are normalized visual coordinates (0-1, origin top-left).
-            // Physical PDF coordinates have origin at bottom-left of the unrotated crop box.
-            // For rotated pages the visual axes map to different physical axes,
-            // so each case must scale against the correct physical dimension.
+            var x = directionX * width;
+            var y = directionY * height;
+
+            // Map from visual space to physical PDF space (origin bottom-left, unrotated).
+            // For rotated pages the visual axes map to different physical axes.
             double finalX, finalY;
             switch (rotation)
             {
                 case Page.Rotate.e_90:
-                    // 90° CW: visual X -> physical Y (scaled by height), visual Y -> physical X (scaled by width)
-                    finalX = directionY * width;
-                    finalY = directionX * height;
+                    finalX = y;
+                    finalY = x;
                     break;

                 case Page.Rotate.e_180:
-                    // 180°: both axes inverted relative to e_0
-                    finalX = (1.0 - directionX) * width;
-                    finalY = directionY * height;
+                    finalX = width - x;
+                    finalY = y;
                     break;

                 case Page.Rotate.e_270:
-                    // 270° CW: visual X -> physical Y inverted (scaled by height), visual Y -> physical X inverted (scaled by width)
-                    finalX = (1.0 - directionY) * width;
-                    finalY = (1.0 - directionX) * height;
+                    finalX = width - y;
+                    finalY = height - x;
                     break;

                 case Page.Rotate.e_0:
                 default:
-                    // Visual X -> physical X (scaled by width), visual Y -> physical Y inverted (scaled by height)
-                    finalX = directionX * width;
-                    finalY = (1.0 - directionY) * height;
+                    finalX = x;
+                    finalY = height - y;
                     break;
             }

